#. +> trunk5
#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_bin.rst:25
msgid "Project Bin"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_bin.rst:42
msgid ""
"The Project Bin\\ [1]_ is a view in Kdenlive which lists all "
"the :term:`assets<Asset>` (clips) that are associated with the project. You "
"can drag files from your OS file manager to the bin, or use the :doc:`Media "
"Browser</project_and_asset_management/media_browser>`."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_bin.rst:44
msgid ""
"It is good practice to use :doc:`folders</project_and_asset_management/"
"project_bin/project_bin_use_folders>`, :doc:`tags</"
"project_and_asset_management/project_bin/project_bin_use_tags>`, and "
"even :doc:`multiple bins</project_and_asset_management/project_bin/"
"project_bin_use_multiple_bins>` to stay organized and have quick and "
"structured access to all assets of the project."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_bin.rst:56
msgid "The initial Project Bin in Kdenlive"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_bin.rst:58
msgid ""
"This is how the project bin looks when you start Kdenlive or create a new "
"project. Note the **Sequence** folder that is there always and will hold all "
"sequences you create."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_bin.rst:60
msgid ""
"The bin essentially consists of the toolbar and the list space. See the "
"project bin :doc:`layout</project_and_asset_management/project_bin/"
"project_bin_use>` for more details."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_bin.rst:71
msgid "An example Project Bin in Kdenlive"
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_bin.rst:73
msgid ""
"This is how the project bin looks with several assets of different types "
"imported, a sequence created, and several folders created by the user."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_bin.rst:75
msgid ""
"From here, you drag the clips into the timeline. Selecting a clip brings it "
"automatically into the Clip Monitor."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_bin.rst:77
msgid ""
"For more details about clip management refer to the :doc:`Clips</"
"project_and_asset_management/project_bin/clips>` chapter."
msgstr ""

#. +> trunk5
#: ../../project_and_asset_management/project_bin.rst:84
msgid ""
"In earlier versions of Kdenlive this view was known as the Project Tree."
msgstr ""

